{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then we would have the-- the-- the soup, and then would be the whole afternoon till the next roll call and evening coffee with nothing to do, and then the whole evening with nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "People who could tell stories, who could summarize, dramatize books, narrators, were in great demand, to try to spend the time, take your mind off your constant hunger.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I did not feel full for two years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not once.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was bloated actually.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some people became very thin, and I looked very healthy, as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was really kind of a bloat, which I lost eventually later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have a predisposition for being rather heavy, [LAUGHS], which is--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is-- it is genetic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- but anyway, occasionally we would manage to get hold of a German newspaper in German, and that would be an occasion for the camp in the evening to come together.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some people who spoke good German would read-- read it, and they would translate it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would-- you'd read between the lines because, of course, the Germans never retreated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They only tightened the-- the lines, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But these people who knew the geography of-- of Europe very well could tell from the names of the towns how the war was going, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things did not change very much during the 22 months.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The big change was that after a year, the Germans started deporting our group again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they deported the people from Lwow alphabetically-- no, all of us, excuse me, alphabetically.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They deported 150 the first week, 150 the next week, and then they stopped.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We never really found out till after the war what had happened.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were S, so we-- we stayed.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
